<p>You can expand the month group by clicking the blue month
name. Adjust the display using the &#39;Mode&#39; drop-down top-
right of the page as required. To return to monthly grouping,
select &#39;Grouped&#39;.

<p>To select an image, click on it to open it in the browser, and click &#39;Mark&#39; above the top right
hand corner of the image. Then click &#39;Close&#39; above the image to return to the normal
browser display.

<hr>
<h3>Marked Images</h3>

<p>Whichever way you use to select pictures, the 'Mark' facility is the best way of temporarily storing your choice. All your 
currently 'Marked' images can be displayed by selecting 'Marked Images' on the main menu.

<p>For the Calendar it is probably sensible to mark a short list of maybe 25-30 images from which to make your final choice. 
Remember that you cannot run multiple marked lists, so if you are likely to want to mark images for a different purpose while 
you are making up your mind on your calendar selection, you will need to save your intermediate selection as a search, which 
can then be retrieved at any time. Any display (e.g. '. . . + links') which shows 'mark' or 'marked' against images displays 
the following options somewhere on the page. 

<p>'View as Search Results' creates a unique search. If you want to add to this 
selection at a later stage, when the selected images are no longer marked, open that search (from 'My recent searches' on the 
main 'Search' page) and 'Mark all images on this page'. You can mark new images to add to your selection, and repeat the above 
stages as required.

<p>
