<p>Once you have created your shortlist of 'marked' images, open the 'Marked Images' page. Click 'Unmark all on this page', then 
select the 12/13 images that you wish to include in the calendar. Note that for ease of creating the calendar, the images 
should be selected in the order in which they will appear in the calendar, as set out in the main calendar instructions.

<hr>
<h3>High Resolution Images</h3>

<p>If you know you will need to add high resolution images, it is probably sensible to adopt the following procedure, before 
you add any of them to the calendar.

<p>1. Create a new folder on your computer for your calendar high-res images.

<p>2. Identify which of the images you have selected need a high resolution version, and locate the originals on your computer.

<p>3. Copy these originals into the new folder, and make any necessary edits (crop/tilt/exposure, etc) to match the version on 
Geograph as closely as possible.

<p>Having all your high resolution images in one folder will make the job of adding them within the calendar creation process 
much more straightforward. (The procedure also ensures that you avoid making unwanted changes to your original images!)


